summary: This document contains detailed descriptions of various telecommunications data records from AT&T, including call and SMS transaction details, device identifiers, and network features. It outlines how calls are processed through AT&T's network and provides definitions for various technical terms and codes used in the records.
keyFacts: The document includes detailed descriptions of call and SMS transaction records from AT&T.
It explains the significance of various identifiers such as IMEI and IMSI in tracking mobile devices.
The document outlines how calls are processed through AT&T's network, including definitions for call types and features.
It mentions that some call records may show zero duration, indicating calls that were not connected.
